    - rid: 138986247837974597
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - What does inertia represent in rotational motion? Which of the following
          best describes it?
        - Which of the following best defines rotational of inertia? Which of the
          following is correct?
        - What property of a body determines how hard it is to start or stop its
          rotation? Which of the following best describes this?
        correctAnswer:
        - The resistance of an object to change its rotational state
        wrongAnswers:
        - The amount of linear force applied on an object
        - The rate of angular displacement per second
        - The energy stored in a rotating object
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974598
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - Torque is considered the rotational counterpart of which quantity? Which
          of the following is correct?
        - Torque in rotational dynamics is similar to which of the following is correct?
        - What is torque most closely related to in linear motion? Which of the following
          is correct?
        correctAnswer:
        - Linear force
        wrongAnswers:
        - Mass
        - Work
        - Displacement
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974599
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - The unit of torque is? Which of the following is correct?
        - Torque is measured in what unit? Which of the following is correct?
        - Which of the following is the correct SI unit of torque?
        correctAnswer:
        - Nm (Newton-Meter)
        wrongAnswers:
        - J (Joule)
        - N (Newton)
        - "kg\xB7m\xB2/s"
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974600
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - A disc with radius 0.2 m and mass 5 kg is rotating. What is its moment
          of inertia?. Which of the following is correct?
        - Which of the following is the moment of inertia of a 5 kg disc with radius
          0.2 m?
        - Which of the following is the moment of inertia of a rotating object with
          mass 5 kg and radius 0.2 m?
        correctAnswer:
        - "0.5 kg\xB7m\xB2"
        wrongAnswers:
        - "0.2 kg\xB7m\xB2"
        - "0.8 kg\xB7m\xB2"
        - "1.0 kg\xB7m\xB2"
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974601
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - "Which of the following is the torque acting on a wheel with moment of
          inertia 3.0 kg\xB7m\xB2 and angular acceleration 2.0 rad/s\xB2?"
        - "Which of the following is the torque on a rotating wheel with moment of
          inertia 3.0 kg\xB7m\xB2 and angular acceleration 2 rad/s\xB2?"
        correctAnswer:
        - 6.0 Nm
        wrongAnswers:
        - 2.0 Nm
        - 3.0 Nm
        - 5.0 Nm
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974602
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - "Which of the following is the angular momentum of a rotating object with
          moment of inertia I = 4.0 kg\xB7m\xB2 and angular velocity w = 5.0 rad/s?"
        - "Which of the following is the angular momentum of a body with I = 4.0
          kg\xB7m\xB2 and \u03C9 = 5.0 rad/s?"
        - "Which of the following is the angular momentum when the moment of inertia
          is 4.0 kg\xB7m\xB2 and the angular velocity is 5.0 rad/s?"
        correctAnswer:
        - "20.0 kg\xB7m\xB2/s"
        wrongAnswers:
        - "10.0 kg\xB7m\xB2/s"
        - "15.0 kg\xB7m\xB2/s"
        - "25.0 kg\xB7m\xB2/s"
        choiceCount: 4
